-- All Nippon Airways May Set Up Kansai-Based Low-Cost Carrier, Yomiuri Says
-- Naoko Fujimura
-- 2010-06-19T08:36:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-19/all-nippon-airways-may-set-up-kansai-based-low-cost-carrier-yomiuri-says.html

          
          
             All Nippon Airways Co. may set up a
low-cost carrier to offer international and domestic flights
from as early as next fiscal year, the Yomiuri newspaper
reported, without saying where it got the information. The
company plans to use the Kansai International Airport in western
Japan as its base for the carrier, the report said.  
          
          


  


        